AGI - Alejandra Rodriguez, a 60-year-old lawyer and journalist, was the winner of Miss Universe Buenos Aires and will fight to represent the country in the international edition of the competition, a fact that immediately spread through social networks. A change in the rules of the competition that every year chooses the most beautiful beauty of the world allowed Rodriguez to participate in the contest in the province of Buenos Aires, prelude to Miss Universe Argentina and the overall contest of Miss Universe.
A few months ago, the organization decreed that, from 2024, the age restriction imposed on competitors to be between 18 and 28 will be abolished. "I am very happy to represent this new paradigm in beauty contests, because we are opening a new phase in which women are not only physical beauty, but another set of values. I am the first of this generation to start with this," said Rodriguez at the El Trece television network.
<div </div
&nbsp;
The lawyer and journalist, born in Brandsen (province of Buenos Aires), said that his secret is based on a healthy lifestyle, on eating well, on being physically active, as well as on normal and not extraordinary care and on some genetics. "What I try to do in general is the intermittent fast, i.e. &nbsp; be for a period of time without eating; I think this helps a lot. I try to eat organic foods, to use good creams and things like that."
Rodriguez now looks at the event of May 25 in Buenos Aires, where he will compete to become the new Miss Universe Argentina and earn a ticket for the international edition of the competition. The South American country won the competition only once, in 1962 with the Norma Nolan model as a candidate; although it boasts two victories in the other global beauty contest, Miss Mondo, in the hands of Norma Cappagli (1960) and Silvana Suarez (1978). &nbsp;
